  • Classes in nz.ac.vuw.ecs.swen225.a3.maze.util used by nz.ac.vuw.ecs.swen225.a3.maze 
    Class and Description
    Direction
    Simple enum for representing direction of an actor, may or may not actually be used by the subclass.
    EventType
    Represents all of the events that can happen in the game, used for firing listeners depending on the event happening
    MoveInfo
    Represents a move in the game
    Position
    Simple util class for recording positions, all coordinates are immutable, this is to ensure we don't get stray pointers to positions of objects and change it by accident
    PrePost
    Simple enum for presenting if an event listener should happen before (pre), or after (post) an action happening
    Type
    Generic Type interface, should be implemented by all enums used to store information about different objects within the game
